values:
tonite is my last night training at ryans, at the end of 
the night we are going to take a test( me and the other
girls training) over serving to see if we are ready to do 
the floor on our own. i hope so. im ready to work by myself.
i am so broke its  not even funny. but thats the life of 
college students, huh. i think i can handle it. well i know i
can. i was a waitress about six years ago but at frisches. ryans
doesnt seem to bad all you really do is get drinks, rolls, make 
your customers happy and bus your tables. and be a people person
and either you are or your not, you know.well i have to be there 
at five so i better hurry to the house so i can be there on time.
i hate rushing.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/13440.html

finals next week all in a lump sum, turn in managements
monday, tuesday's accounting, thusday's math(scary), and
friday's communication. that doesnt sound too bad does 
it. why am i nervous. thats normal, huh. im glad baims
gave us more LJ time, aren't you guys. i have some math 
issues. i have a math tutor to help me out but he has not
met with me this week. both times i went to our meeting 
place this week he hasnt been there. i probably need to 
be giving him a call tonite to make sure we will be able
to do our two meetings next week before exam thursday.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/13138.html

so do we know yet if we are on our last week of LJ or not. 
I just started a job as a server part time at ryans 
steakhouse tonite is my second night. the first night was 
alright. Perfect timing to start though huh. the week before 
finals. oh well. thats how it usually works, overload. ha ha.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/12932.html

I was just in with my math tutor, getting ready 
for my exam tomorrow morning, i got to look over 
things again tonite. i wish i had the rest of the
day to get ready but i have to meet with my group
in west chester(never been there)for a rehearsal 
for our presentation on friday- we are going to do
 a talk show. how exciting huh. i did an alright 
job on my movie critique presentation, actually better
than the actual write-up. well i guess it wasnt too
bad considering it was late. i needed that. i beleive 
we have one more chance thus far for extra credit guess
if we are participating in LJ. that is to do a overview
of our expeirience on LJ this semester, is that right?
well chat with ya tomorrow, enjoy the rest of your day.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/12653.html

im surprised we all didnt get finished with our movie critique
presentations today in management. its all good though. my sister
called me monday and said matt(my brother-in-law) sent another fan
and processor board for my computer. it hasnt came yet, but i cant
wait. I could really use it do some school wsork from home, you
know. well i gotta go. but i be back on tomorrow.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/12297.html

i registered for the summer. im taking three classes. i usually
take the summer off, but i need to knock out some of the miami
courses needed to graduate. i declared a major monday after
class, ha ha, after that reality check in baims class, jus kidding
dont take it personal. it was a good thing for peeps to start 
thinking about that. i am a buisness management student, yes for
that career as an administrator. i do need to make sure summer 
financial aid goes threw or i'll have to drop em and do in the 
fall. but i hope it does though even though tuesdays and thursdays
i will be in classes all day til like 10 at night, seriously. whoa,
what, i dont want to be a student forever guys.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/12183.html

oh yea the end of semester, swamped, i cant see threw the stacks 
of work. im glad me and my partner got our comic strips paper 
finished.movie critique, i think i have all notes i need out of 
the actual movie, i need to take it back its like four days late
now. if i need anything else out of it for the write up, i'll 
have to rent it again. but i probably wont though cause ive watched
it over and over. oh yeah i hope i did ok on the test two in management.
it was kinda harder than the first one,on the chapter four-multiple 
choice. im not complaining though. no no. in accounting he bombarded
us with homework for tuesday. it will be a crammed weekend for homeworks.
its been a long day, thus far, can you tell, ha ha. yea throw a little
humor in there. i need it.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/11842.html

i thought it was supposed to rain today, well it probably will later huh?
yesterday was beautiful. i couldnt stay in the house. Are we all getting 
are movie critiques together. I am half way there but we have a week, im 
glad I have a handle even if it is a little one. its better than not have
worked on it at all, procrastinating. I didnt get a chance to bet the 
deadline for feedback, so ill have to make sure its whats being asked for 
completely. well i will be talking more at ya tomorrow, enjoy your day.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/11727.html

whats up guys. I got my hard drive yesterday, but had to open it open 
because something was rattleing inside of it, the processor fan, ha,
lovely. peices here and there making it hard to just snap back on. clamps
were missing. Ive never even looked inside of a hard drive before, I  
wouldnt wont it to be under these condition that I get to see one. Oh 
this is not good, not good at all. Anything to make harder on me will happen
for sure, im about to explode cause it isnt working and my brother-n-law took
it to minnesota to upgrade all in good faith of helping me. my car and my
computer problems-not resolved yet. i was wanting to get feedback on my
movie critique but i wont be ready to send it before the computer lab closes.
And I have to go get ready for my Exam at 2:30 now so, I guess it only gets better.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/11463.html

just came from accounting class, whoa, professor started off 
slow and now it feels like he's layin it on us. im not complaining
its just a change of pace. Before I went to class I called my mom
and she told me she had had a heart-attack the night before last.
im like trippin "why are you just telling me this". she said I 
had a lot going on and she didnt want to worry me. You gotta be 
kidding me. Im sure she didnt tell my other sister in Minnesota 
so I called and told her, not to worry her, but to inform her of
moms health conditions. I knew she would have wanted to be aware.
Im sure moms will be mad cause I did that but I couldnt help it, I 
was calling her before I thought about it. Moms was gonna keep the 
kids next week ( they will be on spring break ) but im gonna have
to think about that. Im sure she will still want to do it, but i 
wanna see what her physcian says, ya know. well gotta go. I cant 
wait to get my hard drive back from my brother-in-law. I miss the 
the convienence of working at home.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/11139.html

it sure has been nasty weather lately, huh. my sinus's are 
acting up. im in the computer lab for a minute to update my 
livejournal. its been two weeks since ive been on here. my
sister, brother in law, neice and twin nephews were down from
minnesota for spring break. they werent wearing coats, they
felt like it was summer here, haa. well compared to there i 
guess it was. its been two years since ive seen them. my 
computer at home has been giving me shit, so my brother in law
took my hard drive back with him, he's going to send it back 
threw the mail. i dont mean to be inpatient but i cant wait to 
get it back. hes such a good guy. not only is he fixing that,
while he was here he did some work on my car. he did my breaks,
two wheel barrings,and a tyriod. it would have cost me about two
thousand at a shop, it ended up costing me four hundred. he wouldnt
let me give him anything for doing it, he said i have to come up 
there this summer. that doesnt seem fair does it. well gotta go
for now.chat with ya later , class is callin.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/10796.html

we turned in our first test in today in management. im 
pretty sure i did well on all the multiple choice, but 
i hope i did pretty good on the essay question. im sure
i did fine, i always get the jitters when it comes to 
tests. i have my accounting second test im waiting to 
hear how well that went. well holla at cha later
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/10638.html

we (me and the kids) was suppose to go up and see my sister,
my twin nephews, neice and my brother and law  in minnesota 
over the summer.the last time we seen them was two summers ago.
anyways they are coming down here over spring break. its the
brother-in-law's spring break too. me and my sister need to see
each other at least once a year. we had our other sister pass 
away 4 years ago. i am so glad they are coming down. she jus 
called and told me friday. usually we plan sooner than this but
she said "im homesick, i need to see everybody" and thats that. ha
i had car troubles over the summer or not really troubles except it 
wouldnt be able to make it that far and back thats a lenghty ride
buddy. im not jokin neither with kids to, huh fun, but well worth it.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/10258.html

we jus got finished watching Mr. 3000. I liked it. 
my boyfriend really enjoyed it. we watched Open 
Waters before that. Now that movie made me mad.i'm
sorry i dont like when people tell me what happens
in movies so if you dont want to know, dont read 
the next lines. a couple on vacation go out with a 
group diving in the open waters. they dont come back 
on time, specifically told though be back in 35 minutes,
well they get left. well anyways they dont do a whole lot
of swimming to try to get out of the situation,sharks end 
up biting the husband or boyfriend they didnt say,he ends
up giving up and floating off and then she did the same 
not to much longer off he. thats how it ended. that made me
mad. 
we have to do our movie critique, im not sure what movie im 
going to use yet but i'd like to try an hurry an choose it 
in case someone else chooses the movie i do choose. i hope
i do better on this critique than the book one we just did.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/10035.html

Im making cookies at 11 oclock, oh that reminds me let 
me go get them before the burn. Well sometimes they are 
better when their well done. 


I got a Kohls gift certificate for Valentines Day. thats
cool, he probably didnt know what to pick out or got the 
wrong size or something. He did get me some shoes too, I 
have to take them back they fit funny. I got him a new 
coffee pot,wow, huh. I got my boys each a video game.

Were all supposed to go Bowling tomorrow night. My friend
and her son. My boyfriend me and the kids. Its been so long
since I went Bowling. Come to think of it, over 10 years.
This ought to be hillarious. It will be fun though.

I have to take the car to the shop to tommrow after my 2 hour
and 40 minute class. theres nothing not anly forking out all the 
dinaro but sitting there out the shop for a couple hours while 
your car is getting worked on.  Some people will just drop the
car off, im weird like that I like to sit with my car while its
getting worked on. unless of course it has to stay overnight, im
not that weird. ha ha Anyways oh yeah I need  all new tires and
an alignment. ching ching. ching ching.

well im gonna jump off here  for a few. im gettn kinda tired and 
I gotta see the damage of the cookies.

i got one shot out for Mrs. Baim. What about that weather today?
I thought it was quit cold, but im not sure you would agree. You
are use to cooold..... weather.

well were well into the semester and im not doing as well as i wanted to already,
i think i,ll be needing a tutor in my math. i use to love math, but once it starts
getting into all the variables and complex fractions, im confused. i'll gwt threw
this minor set back, real fast. have to. we had our presentations and abstracts 
for our book critiques in management, and they werent all that great turnouts, done
but not great work. now i can relax a little bit when it comes to accounting,thank
god.  we have our first test coming up in management, im trying to be prepared for 
that, im not real sure what to expect and oh yeah book critiques due thursday, good
luck to all.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/9382.html

I went and picked the kids up early from the skating rink, or should i say
snuk up on them. see every month they have a school skating party,and i'll
drop the boys off, and pick them up. One is in the 6th and one in kindergarden.
The only year they'll be in the same school together, isn't that cute. well
anyways let me get back to my story bout sneekn up on the boys. i was sitting
in one of the double sided table in the back. It was so cute my six year old 
rollin around the rink by himself. he was doing such a good job.although he 
did fall a couple of times. that was the first time iv'e seen him be able to
 skate let alone with so much traffic around him. i cant stop giggling thinkin
 bout it. and then their was my 12 year old, which really brought the childhood
 memories back, talking to his freinds, strollin back n forth passin me but 
didnt even see me for about 10 15 minutes. its been so long since iv'e been
skating. i was so glad i went in early to watch them.  They were doin snowball
where the boys be on one side and the girls on the other. it was so fun bein that
energetic and carefree. woo, oh well its fun watchin from this view.

tuesday and the presentations on monday.I may need to get some advise on the

                           beleive that.....

 boys make some cookies in a min. emmm, does't that

That was so funny overhearing to my 12 yr. old talking on the phone today. He had his friend on the phone and they were on with two girls that were on together.

I have to go to conference's for my two boys, cool. My 6 yr. old in Kindergarden is doing great. 
My 12 yr. old in 6th grade could be doing better, he's letting his friends get to him. Well then 
leaving I backed into a car. I (we) then had to wait for someone to come out cause there appeared 
to be a mark on the back bumper. The mom and son came out and her son wiped the mark right off,whoa.
Ok so we get home and the boys start their regular arguments. Something about helping clean up their room. Here they come with mom he's this, he's that. I just threw my hands up and said, OK GO to the room the both of ya and dont even open that door until you guy's are getting along. I've had enough!
I'ts only 5 oclock its time to make dinner, and hopefully have a less crazy night.

Is that what they say when you make a big deal over something so minor.Well

tired.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/7376.html

oh well this will be my last year of my 20's. i hate to say it and didnt see it com'n but in two weeks i will be 29 years old. i dont know if i want to celebrate  or what. my kids are gett'n older, my youngest will be 5 on wednesday. ive gotta throw him a big oh bash. gosh what it would be like to go back to them days. not fearing nothing. my oldest will be 11 next month. i get to think'n about so much. no turn'n back.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/6976.html

last saturday morning i woke up and was getting ready to go to the store for some stuff to make my lasanga and i needed cigarettes, when my key would not fit in the ignition.  my key was mangled up, one of my boys was playing with it in one of the doors in the house. so i had to call good oh ma to run me around to all the places that i needed to go for the rest of the weekend because my key has to be made by the dealership i got the car from and the parts department wasnt open until monday. all my plans basically down the drain. i had plans to go pick up the kids friends to spend the night and was going to go to the movies that night. well had to put all that off. later that night i took some viscripts(i know i didnt spell that right) and pulled and tuugged around with the key to see if i could straighten out.well it worked but was a little snug. i still couldnt drive around  because i didnt want to damage the ignition. on my way to get a key made monday, i stopped to get gas, got back in the car and my key went in but it wouldnt turn. i had to call a ride to come get me while leaving my car at the pump. i went to get the key made the guy gave it to me for free because he thought i was going to need a new ignition,cylinder
 oh my nerves was bad. he said when i try this key and if it dont work, try wiggaling on the steering wheel. well i tried it and even the steering wheel thing and it still didnt work. oh i knew it, until some man came over to try, got to wiggalin on the wheel and what do ya know, the damn thing started. i wanted to give him a big oh kiss,, but we all know you jus cant give a total stranger a kiss. that was a crazy expierence that i do not want to ever happen again. its all good now though.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/6806.html

i am not on this cold weather, for real, this is too much. the wind has been crazy. i was drivin on 75 last night and the wind damn near knocked me off the road. i thought i was gonna get pulled over for weavin. before i got a reliable ride, i dont know how i did it. i feel like a cry baby but damn its cold. And then after this why did my sister call me today,asking if i'll come down to minnesota for christmas. not to mention i probably cant afford it, but its too cold. well this was her reply to that. well maybe then you can get a little feel for it for when you come here to stay. i told her to let me think about it. gosh, it took me about 90 dollars for the gas inthe summer, lord knows what it will be like in the winter, with the heater runnin the whole time. i'm not sure how the roads will be neither.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/6563.html
we got the day off in accounting. that is cool we have a take home quiz to do and return back on tues. its not to often the teacher cancels class.  ya know. have a good weekend.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/6350.html

that was alright, the quiz. i wonder how this will turn out. we didnt have much time to do it, good thing we were able to compare or i dont think i would have got it all finished. i hope we all did ok.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/5950.html

oh yeah we had fun this trick or treat night. my youngest was not at all tired. he was runn'n faster than my oldest. he kept saying "who's the master" to his bubby. but by time it was over he was crashed for the night. my oldest started havin trouble see'n threw his hair on his scary mask. needless to say one more haloween down. i need to take my yard decorations down. i know i should have done it already. i jus look and pass right by em.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/5840.html

so are we done with the nice weather. time to break out the winter coats,gloves ,hats.im sure not ready, but i guess you could say ready to get it over with,ha. i hate cold weather. im glad my car has heaters in the seats well jus the front seats. that sucks for the people in the back. oh well.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/5564.html

at the rate im going here at miami i'll be here for another at least 3 or 4 years. im 29-next-month.single with my two boys. by the way i go for a child support hearing next mont,ya.its just not gonna cut it i dont think. i got the application ive been requesting in the mail yesterday, for the LPN program at a vocational school, right outside of town.so im fillin that out. if i can get in that. i can always do a fast track for the RN. And sometimes your employer will pay for it. i signed up for my classes here next semester. we'll see how the cookie crumbles.i think im keeping focused. when you have those babies, you have to take care of them. well some dont but that makes me even wanna work harder ya dig.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/5170.html

i have two sisters but one passed away two years ago in an automobile accident. the youngest Amy she was 22 at the time. im not gett'n sobby its hard to say more than that if ya feel me. anyways so i have my other sister left melony but she lives in st. paul minnesota shes a year younger than me. she refuses to move back home.i talked to her yesterday on the phone and she was telling me that her and my twin nephews were sick and stay'n in the house. she said its gettn kinda cold. ha,really. and she was tellin me that my neice Brianna jus started girl scouts, she's six.when i was up there over the summer she asked me, aunt felicia why are you leaving. that sucks thats the only neices and nephews(and sister) i have and i see them like once a year if that. i dont know how long this will be an issue. It just is so cold there. i dont even know if i wanna go. its jus so much change i dont even think about it, well i do, i jus keep pushin it off.i dont know if i wanna finish school and maybe by then she will change her mind. no i know she wont come back to ohio. she likes it there. i spent a week there this summer. but like i said that was the summer. the people there are so nice. there arent alot of snobby people that ive encountered in last couple visits i had. i dont know, it feels good talkin about it though.
http://fee-mommie.livejournal.com/4902.html

miami's daycare had their halloween party today. jayson was walking in the halls, i waived at him and he was jus hav'n to much fun. he was a liitle upset ealier because he couldn't wear his costume to school, he had to wait until two to put it on. he was like mom they dont know how to do my costume. he got over it though. all the kids were so cute. oh yeah, i dont ever dress up but i guess i will be this year my aunt is throwing a halloween party and every one will be dressed . why am i gonna be a butterfly. yepee. oh lord. this outta be a sight. ha. well i'll have to update you on that one. i have to buy the finishing touches  before saturday or i'll try to dodge the whole scene, my aunt would kill me.

jayson,4, is out of all things a cowboy. thats another thing i was trippin when thats what he picked out. he looks cute though. jay jay,10, a scary mask with green and black hair and a cape.
ive had to threatin to take away, he keeps scaring jayson. he does look scary too.

what is everyone else doing this year staying in and passing out candy, that sounds like a good idea. but its fun to run around with the kids especially if you have little ones. i think ill do a mixture of both cause i know jayson wont last the whole time. well he might jus surprise me.

i had promised i would take my oldest to the haunted house. so thats what i did saturday. we went to the temple of terror,they had a trail to but i was to scared and didnt feel all that good and neither did he. if you were clausterfobic you couldnt have went. you couldnt see in there and it was like a maze or something.there was dead ends,which i bumped my nogg'n a couple of times. i made him hold my hand. they get to blow'n that smoke and its cool but i think they be goin a little overboard with it when you be all enhal'n it in your throat. im cool with them  jump'n out at ya too, but when they jus stand their im like ok you scared me,Go.chainsaw's though thats scary they are jus so loud. we had fun.

it was although a little different from the other movies they've had. you'd have to see it and compare them to understand. and i know how i am about people telling the scenes, so i wont go there.
